Foreign Trade of Major Chinese Regions: Chongqing 
Xinhua is releasing major economic indicators of ten major Chinese
regions on a quarterly and annual basis. The ten regions are:
Guangdong, Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang, Henan, Liaoning, Shanghai,
Beijing, Tianjin, and Chongqing. These provinces and municipalities
make up the bulk of the Chinese economy.
The following is the foreign trade performance in Chongqing, one of
China's four municipalities, in the first three quarters of this year:
The total foreign trade volume in Chongqing reached 1.352 billion U.S.
dollars in the three-quarter period, rising 8.4 percent over the same
period in 2000.
The total trade volume included 792 million U.S. dollars in exports, up
15.9 percent, and 560 million U.S. dollars in imports, down 0.6
percent.
